messages.message: Thanks @Serena! @Vishnu do we do anything similar for list extractions?
not at the moment. we do not compare information across large portions of the document, we break them into chunks and deal with each chunk independently in the current implementation.

For 3a I think this might be what some customers are experiencing. If even a tiny amount of the page is on the screen then you don't get dragged (you don't know whether to scroll down, up, or if there is a provenance issue).

It makes more logical sense for me that if the bounding box isn't on the page then you should be dragged @Serena
